George A. WALLACE et al. v. Wm. H. TUGGLE, Trustee in Bankruptcy of Escalon Winery, Inc. No. 9765. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 13, 1941. Albert Picard, of San Francisco, Cal., and O..C. Parkinson, of Stockton, Cal., for appellants. Edward F. Treadwell and Reginald S. Laughlin, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate of this court issued forthwith.
